<p>Longavesnes<br/>[September 1918]<br/>Sun 29<br/>The big fight commenced at 4 50 Am<br/>30 Mon<br/>The winter came in like a wolf on the fold, his winds they are bighting his frost "Oh so cold!<br/>1 Oct Tues<br/>Going into action all roads leading to the line are nought but a seething mass of traffic having dinner at HAGINCOURT<br/>2 Wed<br/>Now at the Hindenburg line at Ribequete and what I've seen "Oh God", makes a man sick with horror</p>
